# Well-Architected — six pillars

The structured answer to *"is this architecture good?"* — 13 modules of services, now composed.

| Pillar | Answers |
|---|---|
| **Operational Excellence** | run & improve day to day? |
| **Security** | data & identities protected? |
| **Reliability** | uptime & recovery targets met? |
| **Performance Efficiency** | fast without overspending? |
| **Cost Optimization** | paying only for value? |
| **Sustainability** | minimising footprint? |

## The key idea

The pillars are **not independent** — security ↔ cost, reliability ↔ cost, sustainability ≈ cost.

The **review process makes trade-offs explicit per workload** — no silently optimising one pillar at another's expense. *Naming the trade-off and choosing* **is** the architect's job.
